text: Oakland is an unincorporated community located within Alloway Township in Salem County, New Jersey, United States.Locality Search, State of New Jersey. Oakland was named after a white oak tree grove. The vicinity used to have a stop on the West Jersey and Seashore Railroad which was known as Oakland Station. ==References== Category:Alloway Township, New Jersey Category:Unincorporated communities in Salem County, New Jersey Category:Unincorporated communities in New Jersey
